  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "4. the house of Baal-berith—either the temple, or the place where this idol was worshipped; Baal-berith, \"god of the covenant,\" by invocation of whom the league of cities was formed.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Abimelech hired vain and light persons, which followed him—idle, worthless vagabonds, the scum of society, who had nothing to lose, but much to gain from the success of a revolutionary movement.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Poole's Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Threescore and ten, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " agreeably to the number of his enemies, Gideon’s seventy sons. ",
        "children": []
